17

); hind tibia bearing two sets of perpendicular setae at the apex (

Fig. 
17

).

Body covered with very long, recumbent silvery setae, especially on posterior corners of head, pronotum and abdominal tergites I–III (
Fig. 18
).

Body wider; legs lacking spines, grasping comb absent. Abdominal tergite VIII widened and flattened bearing long, erect, brown setae along lateral and posterior margins (

Fig. 
18

). Ventrite VII with rounded apex (

